Package: reflimR
Type: Package
Title: Reference Limit Estimation Using Routine Laboratory Data
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2023-12-06
Author: Georg Hoffmann, Sandra Klawitter, Frank Klawonn
Maintainer: Georg Hoffmann <georg.hoffmann@trillium.de>
Description: Uses an indirect method based on truncated quantile-quantile plots to estimate reference limits from routine laboratory data.
    The principle of the method was developed in 1963 by Robert G Hoffmann and modified by Georg Hoffmann and colleagues in 2015, 2020, and 2022. 
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    stats, graphics, grDevices
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
URL: https://github.com/reflim/reflimR
BugReports: https://github.com/reflim/reflimR/issues
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Roxygen: list(markdown=TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
